  <text>
      <body>
        
     
      <div xml:id="itaughtmyselftolivesimply"> 
              <interpGrp type="poembox">
                <interp ana="#form" type="free"></interp>
                <interp ana="#tone" type="other"></interp>
                <interp ana="#topic" type="society"></interp>
              </interpGrp>
             <lg> 
               <l>I taught myself to live simply and wisely,</l>
               <l>to look at the sky and pray to God,</l> 
               <l>and to wander long before evening</l>
               <l>to tire my superfluous worries.</l>
               <l>When the burdocks rustle in the ravine</l>
               <l>and the yellow-red rowanberry cluster droops</l>
               <l>I compose happy verses</l>
               <l>about life's decay, decay and beauty.</l>
               <l>I come back. The fluffy cat</l>
               <l>licks my palm, purrs so sweetly</l>
               <l>and the fire flares bright</l>
               <l>on the saw-mill turret by the lake.</l>
               <l>Only the cry of a stork landing on the roof</l>
               <l>occasionally breaks the silence.</l>
               <l>If you knock on my door</l>
               <l>I may not even hear.</l>  
               <!-- You can put comments or notes to yourself in like this -->
             </lg>
